The Conductor doesn't delegate to other agents — what's wrong? <p>The most common cause is the subagent orchestration setting not being enabled. Add this to your VS Code User Settings (not workspace settings):</p> <pre><code>{
  "chat.customAgentInSubagent.enabled": true
}
</code></pre> <p>See Troubleshooting for detailed steps.</p> Where do I report bugs or request features? <ul> <li>Bugs: GitHub Issues</li> <li>Questions: GitHub Discussions</li> <li>Feature requests: Open a GitHub issue with the <code>enhancement</code> label</li> </ul> What happens if an agent produces bad output? <p>Use specific follow-up prompts to correct the issue. For example: "The VNet address space conflicts with our on-premises range. Change to 172.16.0.0/16." If the error persists, start a fresh chat session — context accumulation can degrade output quality. The Troubleshooting guide covers common failure modes and recovery steps.</p> What if MCP servers are unreachable? <p>The workflow degrades gracefully. Steps 1-5 can proceed without MCP — agents skip real-time pricing lookups and use documented defaults. Only Step 2 cost estimation and Step 7 as-built cost updates depend directly on the Pricing MCP server. Governance discovery (Step 3.5) uses Azure REST API, not MCP.</p> <p>Step 6 (Deploy) requires Azure credentials</p> <p>If you attempt deployment without an active Azure subscription and <code>az login</code>, the deploy agent will fail with an authentication error. See Troubleshooting for recovery steps.</p> <p>See also: Troubleshooting · Prompt Guide · Glossary</p>
